WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.434 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.434 --> 00:00:07.410 align:middle line:90%
[CHIMING]

00:00:07.410 --> 00:00:09.386 align:middle line:90%


00:00:09.386 --> 00:00:11.856 align:middle line:10%
[INSTRUMENTAL ETHEREAL MUSIC]

00:00:11.856 --> 00:00:23.730 align:middle line:90%


00:00:23.730 --> 00:00:26.340 align:middle line:10%
>> My name is Erich von Daniken.

00:00:26.340 --> 00:00:27.450 align:middle line:10%
I am Swiss.

00:00:27.450 --> 00:00:33.770 align:middle line:10%
I'm the author of "Chariots of
the Gods," and 40 other books.

00:00:33.770 --> 00:00:36.875 align:middle line:84%
All these books have
the same subject.

00:00:36.875 --> 00:00:39.450 align:middle line:90%


00:00:39.450 --> 00:00:42.590 align:middle line:10%
Were extraterrestrials here
thousands of years ago?

00:00:42.590 --> 00:00:46.320 align:middle line:90%


00:00:46.320 --> 00:00:49.820 align:middle line:84%
I was educated in Switzerland
as a strict Catholic,

00:00:49.820 --> 00:00:53.690 align:middle line:84%
in a boarding school
led by Jesuits.

00:00:53.690 --> 00:00:56.630 align:middle line:84%
Of course, I was in
deep believer in God.

00:00:56.630 --> 00:00:59.930 align:middle line:84%
I still am a believer in
God, although, I do not

00:00:59.930 --> 00:01:01.530 align:middle line:90%
know what God really is.

00:01:01.530 --> 00:01:05.510 align:middle line:84%
But when I was a boy,
17-years-old, God, for me,

00:01:05.510 --> 00:01:07.030 align:middle line:90%
had to have some qualities.

00:01:07.030 --> 00:01:10.040 align:middle line:84%
For example, God
makes no mistake.

00:01:10.040 --> 00:01:13.220 align:middle line:84%
God does not need a vehicle in
which to move around from point

00:01:13.220 --> 00:01:15.500 align:middle line:90%
A to point B. God is all over.

00:01:15.500 --> 00:01:18.030 align:middle line:90%


00:01:18.030 --> 00:01:20.190 align:middle line:84%
Now, in this boarding
school, we have

00:01:20.190 --> 00:01:23.040 align:middle line:84%
to translate parts of the
Bible from Latin into Greek,

00:01:23.040 --> 00:01:24.660 align:middle line:90%
and from Greek to German.

00:01:24.660 --> 00:01:27.010 align:middle line:84%
Then I learned
that in the Bible,

00:01:27.010 --> 00:01:29.190 align:middle line:84%
the God, which is
described there,

00:01:29.190 --> 00:01:32.760 align:middle line:84%
he uses a vehicle
to move around.

00:01:32.760 --> 00:01:35.120 align:middle line:84%
He descends on the holy
mountain with smoke,

00:01:35.120 --> 00:01:38.060 align:middle line:84%
and fire, and trembling,
and loud noise, and so on,

00:01:38.060 --> 00:01:40.320 align:middle line:90%
and he made some mistakes.

00:01:40.320 --> 00:01:45.720 align:middle line:84%
So all of a sudden, I had doubts
in my own Catholic education,

00:01:45.720 --> 00:01:49.100 align:middle line:84%
and I simply wanted to find
out if other communities

00:01:49.100 --> 00:01:51.800 align:middle line:84%
in antiquity have
similar traditions

00:01:51.800 --> 00:01:54.050 align:middle line:84%
than we have it
from the Christian

00:01:54.050 --> 00:01:55.610 align:middle line:90%
and the Jewish tradition.

00:01:55.610 --> 00:01:59.090 align:middle line:84%
That was the beginning of
"Chariots of the Gods."

00:01:59.090 --> 00:02:01.730 align:middle line:90%
A long time ago, over 50 years.

00:02:01.730 --> 00:02:04.430 align:middle line:90%


00:02:04.430 --> 00:02:09.490 align:middle line:84%
In the meantime, I'm
an 84-year-old man.

00:02:09.490 --> 00:02:14.200 align:middle line:84%
Of course, I'm married since
58 years with the same wife.

00:02:14.200 --> 00:02:18.070 align:middle line:84%
I have two grandchildren,
and I am happy to be alive,

00:02:18.070 --> 00:02:21.038 align:middle line:90%
and to work as I do it.

00:02:21.038 --> 00:02:22.400 align:middle line:10%
[JAZZ MUSIC]

00:02:22.400 --> 00:02:26.610 align:middle line:10%
Well, as every child,
I was not different,

00:02:26.610 --> 00:02:28.860 align:middle line:10%
except I was always a musician.

00:02:28.860 --> 00:02:32.040 align:middle line:84%
I was always trying to
play some instruments.

00:02:32.040 --> 00:02:35.040 align:middle line:90%
Now, as a small boy, the drums.

00:02:35.040 --> 00:02:37.050 align:middle line:84%
And later, growing
up in school, the

00:02:37.050 --> 00:02:39.270 align:middle line:84%
trumpet, and of
course, the piano.

00:02:39.270 --> 00:02:42.840 align:middle line:84%
Of course, even as a boy,
I was a member of a band.

00:02:42.840 --> 00:02:44.670 align:middle line:90%
A jazz band at that time.

00:02:44.670 --> 00:02:48.390 align:middle line:84%
If I would not have become
a best selling author,

00:02:48.390 --> 00:02:51.960 align:middle line:84%
my career would have gone
in the direction of music.

00:02:51.960 --> 00:02:55.980 align:middle line:90%


00:02:55.980 --> 00:02:59.220 align:middle line:10%
For my family, we came
from the hotel business.

00:02:59.220 --> 00:03:01.710 align:middle line:10%
My grandmother had a
hotel with the restaurant.

00:03:01.710 --> 00:03:05.370 align:middle line:84%
So I was growing up in the
hotel and restaurant business,

00:03:05.370 --> 00:03:08.670 align:middle line:84%
and of course, I made
first my high school,

00:03:08.670 --> 00:03:10.890 align:middle line:84%
the boarding school
in the French speaking

00:03:10.890 --> 00:03:14.440 align:middle line:90%
part of Switzerland.

00:03:14.440 --> 00:03:16.900 align:middle line:10%
So six years in that
boarding school.

00:03:16.900 --> 00:03:19.600 align:middle line:90%


00:03:19.600 --> 00:03:21.610 align:middle line:84%
In the boarding school,
we had, for example,

00:03:21.610 --> 00:03:24.540 align:middle line:90%
translated part of the Bible.

00:03:24.540 --> 00:03:26.990 align:middle line:10%
It's the second book in Moses.

00:03:26.990 --> 00:03:30.410 align:middle line:84%
Before the lord descends
on the holy mountain,

00:03:30.410 --> 00:03:34.520 align:middle line:84%
he gives order to Moses that
Moses should create a gate

00:03:34.520 --> 00:03:37.250 align:middle line:84%
around the holy mountain,
otherwise the Israelites

00:03:37.250 --> 00:03:38.600 align:middle line:90%
would be destroyed.

00:03:38.600 --> 00:03:43.440 align:middle line:10%
So Moses constructs a
gate, and then the Lord

00:03:43.440 --> 00:03:47.190 align:middle line:10%
descends with smoke, and fire,
and rumbling, and loud noise.

00:03:47.190 --> 00:03:50.430 align:middle line:90%


00:03:50.430 --> 00:03:54.760 align:middle line:84%
So I said to myself, my
god, the real Almighty

00:03:54.760 --> 00:03:58.090 align:middle line:84%
God of all religion, that
the spirit of the universe

00:03:58.090 --> 00:04:01.640 align:middle line:84%
does not need to construct,
first, a gate for safety.

00:04:01.640 --> 00:04:04.810 align:middle line:84%
Does not come down with smoke,
and fire, and loud noise.

00:04:04.810 --> 00:04:07.870 align:middle line:10%
So I had my doubts in
that boarding school,

00:04:07.870 --> 00:04:10.960 align:middle line:10%
and of course, I was talking
to this to my professors.

00:04:10.960 --> 00:04:12.160 align:middle line:90%
And they were not afraid.

00:04:12.160 --> 00:04:14.830 align:middle line:84%
They said Erich, if you
think in this direction,

00:04:14.830 --> 00:04:18.880 align:middle line:84%
you should learn much more
about the old scriptures

00:04:18.880 --> 00:04:20.200 align:middle line:90%
before you discuss this.

00:04:20.200 --> 00:04:24.730 align:middle line:84%
And they told me, Erich, go to
father whatever the name was,

00:04:24.730 --> 00:04:27.280 align:middle line:90%
and ask for a Book of Enoch.

00:04:27.280 --> 00:04:28.900 align:middle line:90%
I asked for a Book of Enoch.

00:04:28.900 --> 00:04:30.690 align:middle line:90%
I read the Book of Enoch.

00:04:30.690 --> 00:04:32.185 align:middle line:90%
I was completely confused.

00:04:32.185 --> 00:04:42.060 align:middle line:90%


00:04:42.060 --> 00:04:44.370 align:middle line:10%
You know, Enoch in
the Bible, you simply

00:04:44.370 --> 00:04:46.530 align:middle line:10%
hear that he was
the first human who

00:04:46.530 --> 00:04:49.650 align:middle line:10%
disappeared in a fiery
chariot from this planet,

00:04:49.650 --> 00:04:53.820 align:middle line:10%
and they say he was the seventh
patriarch before the Great

00:04:53.820 --> 00:04:54.870 align:middle line:10%
Flood.

00:04:54.870 --> 00:04:59.880 align:middle line:84%
Now, roughly 180 years
ago, a British explorer

00:04:59.880 --> 00:05:03.210 align:middle line:84%
came to Ethiopia,
and in Ethiopia, he

00:05:03.210 --> 00:05:04.730 align:middle line:90%
came into an old library.

00:05:04.730 --> 00:05:07.930 align:middle line:84%
And in this old library, he
found the book with the title

00:05:07.930 --> 00:05:09.870 align:middle line:90%
The Book of Enoch.

00:05:09.870 --> 00:05:12.330 align:middle line:10%
Slowly, he translated
the Book of Enoch

00:05:12.330 --> 00:05:14.520 align:middle line:10%
from the Ethiopian
language into English.

00:05:14.520 --> 00:05:16.260 align:middle line:10%
Later, from English into German.

00:05:16.260 --> 00:05:19.140 align:middle line:10%
And I was a boy, I had
the German translation

00:05:19.140 --> 00:05:23.970 align:middle line:10%
before my eyes, and I
was completely shocked

00:05:23.970 --> 00:05:26.670 align:middle line:10%
because Enoch speaks
in the first person.

00:05:26.670 --> 00:05:28.100 align:middle line:90%
An eyewitness.

00:05:28.100 --> 00:05:29.700 align:middle line:90%
Not in the third person.

00:05:29.700 --> 00:05:32.490 align:middle line:90%
He says he was 12 years old.

00:05:32.490 --> 00:05:35.190 align:middle line:84%
The whole community of the
village wanted to go to sleep.

00:05:35.190 --> 00:05:37.530 align:middle line:84%
Then they hear the
noise in the sky.

00:05:37.530 --> 00:05:39.640 align:middle line:90%
They saw a light in the sky.

00:05:39.640 --> 00:05:41.910 align:middle line:84%
All of a sudden,
the light fell down

00:05:41.910 --> 00:05:44.170 align:middle line:84%
to the earth, and all the
inhabitants of the village

00:05:44.170 --> 00:05:44.970 align:middle line:90%
runaway.

00:05:44.970 --> 00:05:46.950 align:middle line:90%
They were afraid, except Enoch.

00:05:46.950 --> 00:05:49.890 align:middle line:84%
He says I stood there
in astonishment.

00:05:49.890 --> 00:05:53.040 align:middle line:84%
Then, all of a sudden, two
beings came close to me

00:05:53.040 --> 00:05:55.830 align:middle line:90%
in glittering clothes.

00:05:55.830 --> 00:05:59.100 align:middle line:84%
And he says, clearly,
these two beings

00:05:59.100 --> 00:06:01.830 align:middle line:90%
did not look like humans.

00:06:01.830 --> 00:06:04.530 align:middle line:10%
They did not breath like humans.

00:06:04.530 --> 00:06:05.970 align:middle line:90%
They breathed differently.

00:06:05.970 --> 00:06:09.130 align:middle line:84%
I never saw beings
like this on Earth.

00:06:09.130 --> 00:06:10.150 align:middle line:90%
He is afraid.

00:06:10.150 --> 00:06:12.570 align:middle line:84%
Enoch, finally, he fells
on this ground too.

00:06:12.570 --> 00:06:17.640 align:middle line:84%
Then, somebody picks him up,
and says to him, "Son of humans,

00:06:17.640 --> 00:06:19.170 align:middle line:90%
don't be afraid.

00:06:19.170 --> 00:06:20.640 align:middle line:90%
We won't hurt you."

00:06:20.640 --> 00:06:22.230 align:middle line:84%
And then follows
the whole story.

00:06:22.230 --> 00:06:24.930 align:middle line:84%
An incredible story
in the Book of Enoch.

00:06:24.930 --> 00:06:28.230 align:middle line:84%
So I was completely
fascinated of Enoch.

00:06:28.230 --> 00:06:31.530 align:middle line:84%
And later, of course, I learned
that we find similar stories

00:06:31.530 --> 00:06:33.330 align:middle line:90%
in the Maya texts.

00:06:33.330 --> 00:06:35.850 align:middle line:10%
The same thing happen
in the old Indian text.

00:06:35.850 --> 00:06:39.660 align:middle line:90%
Always one person is taken out.

00:06:39.660 --> 00:06:43.790 align:middle line:84%
Also they learned the
language of the strangers.

00:06:43.790 --> 00:06:46.380 align:middle line:10%
Enoch receives a writing device.

00:06:46.380 --> 00:06:48.720 align:middle line:90%
Then they dictate in books--

00:06:48.720 --> 00:06:53.550 align:middle line:84%
books about science, astronomy,
calendar, engineering,

00:06:53.550 --> 00:06:55.280 align:middle line:90%
and all this.

00:06:55.280 --> 00:06:58.620 align:middle line:84%
Now, the critics cannot
say, this is ridiculous.

00:06:58.620 --> 00:07:02.640 align:middle line:84%
How should extraterrestrials
speak Enoch's language?

00:07:02.640 --> 00:07:05.520 align:middle line:84%
In our time, our
ethnologists, they

00:07:05.520 --> 00:07:09.060 align:middle line:84%
were visiting some tribe
from the upper Amazon River

00:07:09.060 --> 00:07:11.040 align:middle line:84%
or maybe on the
Upper Nile River.

00:07:11.040 --> 00:07:13.380 align:middle line:10%
It was never a
problem of learning

00:07:13.380 --> 00:07:16.440 align:middle line:10%
the language of the natives
within a short period.

00:07:16.440 --> 00:07:19.020 align:middle line:84%
After five, six months,
our ethnologists

00:07:19.020 --> 00:07:21.060 align:middle line:84%
understood the
languages of the tribe.

00:07:21.060 --> 00:07:24.170 align:middle line:90%


00:07:24.170 --> 00:07:26.790 align:middle line:84%
These extraterrestrials,
they behaved themselves

00:07:26.790 --> 00:07:28.710 align:middle line:90%
like ethnologists would do.

00:07:28.710 --> 00:07:32.220 align:middle line:84%
They studied their group
before visiting them.

00:07:32.220 --> 00:07:35.520 align:middle line:84%
So I'm not shocked at all
if the stranger speaks

00:07:35.520 --> 00:07:38.220 align:middle line:90%
to Enoch in Enoch's language.

00:07:38.220 --> 00:07:40.680 align:middle line:84%
And the stranger says to
Enoch, don't be afraid.

00:07:40.680 --> 00:07:43.710 align:middle line:84%
And he says, if you wish,
you can come with us.

00:07:43.710 --> 00:07:45.200 align:middle line:90%
We teach you.

00:07:45.200 --> 00:07:51.300 align:middle line:84%
Enoch says yes, I
wish to be teached.

00:07:51.300 --> 00:07:53.220 align:middle line:90%
He receives an aura.

00:07:53.220 --> 00:07:56.610 align:middle line:84%
Something like the same
spacesuit which they had on.

00:07:56.610 --> 00:07:57.830 align:middle line:90%
Then they go up.

00:07:57.830 --> 00:08:01.980 align:middle line:84%
He describes over the Earth,
I saw the round Earth,

00:08:01.980 --> 00:08:03.840 align:middle line:90%
and I saw gigantic things.

00:08:03.840 --> 00:08:06.840 align:middle line:84%
He compares them with
brilliance, with diamonds,

00:08:06.840 --> 00:08:07.740 align:middle line:90%
and so on.

00:08:07.740 --> 00:08:10.200 align:middle line:90%
Doors open, doors close.

00:08:10.200 --> 00:08:11.500 align:middle line:90%
They go in there.

00:08:11.500 --> 00:08:14.040 align:middle line:84%
He passes through
strange gardens

00:08:14.040 --> 00:08:16.020 align:middle line:84%
with vegetables
and flowers, which

00:08:16.020 --> 00:08:18.030 align:middle line:90%
he had never seen on Earth.

00:08:18.030 --> 00:08:20.220 align:middle line:84%
Then he comes into a
big room, and there

00:08:20.220 --> 00:08:22.560 align:middle line:84%
in the center of the
room, there was a throne.

00:08:22.560 --> 00:08:25.980 align:middle line:84%
And on this throne, the
highest was sitting.

00:08:25.980 --> 00:08:29.210 align:middle line:84%
When the three came in there,
two of the extraterrestrials

00:08:29.210 --> 00:08:31.770 align:middle line:84%
and Enoch, the
highest stands up,

00:08:31.770 --> 00:08:35.760 align:middle line:84%
walks a few steps toward
Enoch, shakes his hand,

00:08:35.760 --> 00:08:40.539 align:middle line:84%
and says to him, welcome
here at our place.

00:08:40.539 --> 00:08:43.900 align:middle line:84%
Now, what I just told you is
part of the Book of Enoch,

00:08:43.900 --> 00:08:49.510 align:middle line:84%
but not the way I told it to
you because some 160 years ago,

00:08:49.510 --> 00:08:52.750 align:middle line:84%
when Enoch was translated first
from the Ethiopian language

00:08:52.750 --> 00:08:55.510 align:middle line:84%
into English, all these
brilliant professors

00:08:55.510 --> 00:08:58.900 align:middle line:84%
at that time, they knew
nothing about space travel,

00:08:58.900 --> 00:09:01.960 align:middle line:84%
nothing about space ships,
nothing about flying.

00:09:01.960 --> 00:09:05.170 align:middle line:84%
So they believed we have
to see all these things

00:09:05.170 --> 00:09:06.910 align:middle line:90%
in a religious context.

00:09:06.910 --> 00:09:10.210 align:middle line:84%
So the translation is
different to what I say.

00:09:10.210 --> 00:09:18.510 align:middle line:90%


00:09:18.510 --> 00:09:22.390 align:middle line:84%
I am a deep believer in
God, and all these things--

00:09:22.390 --> 00:09:24.710 align:middle line:90%
what is handed down--

00:09:24.710 --> 00:09:28.050 align:middle line:90%
is not belonging to God.

00:09:28.050 --> 00:09:30.880 align:middle line:90%
God is omnipotent.

00:09:30.880 --> 00:09:34.810 align:middle line:84%
Imagine for a second that
my idea would be correct.

00:09:34.810 --> 00:09:37.330 align:middle line:84%
So we were visited by
beings from outer space.

00:09:37.330 --> 00:09:41.140 align:middle line:84%
The next question is where
did these visitors come from?

00:09:41.140 --> 00:09:42.460 align:middle line:90%
What is their evolution?

00:09:42.460 --> 00:09:44.950 align:middle line:84%
Have they been influenced
by another solar system?

00:09:44.950 --> 00:09:47.090 align:middle line:84%
OK, where did the
other come from?

00:09:47.090 --> 00:09:47.980 align:middle line:90%
And so on.

00:09:47.980 --> 00:09:50.950 align:middle line:84%
You can play it back
again for thousands,

00:09:50.950 --> 00:09:52.510 align:middle line:90%
hundreds of thousands of years.

00:09:52.510 --> 00:09:55.060 align:middle line:84%
Finally, you arrive
to a starting point,

00:09:55.060 --> 00:09:58.750 align:middle line:84%
where in every respect with
region, you have to confess

00:09:58.750 --> 00:10:00.910 align:middle line:90%
and to say, here is God.

00:10:00.910 --> 00:10:02.140 align:middle line:90%
Here is the beginning.

00:10:02.140 --> 00:10:03.400 align:middle line:90%
Here is the spirit.

00:10:03.400 --> 00:10:04.990 align:middle line:90%
So you never lose God.

00:10:04.990 --> 00:10:07.210 align:middle line:90%
I never lost my God.

00:10:07.210 --> 00:10:10.870 align:middle line:84%
I am one of these figures
who still pray every evening,

00:10:10.870 --> 00:10:13.650 align:middle line:84%
but my prayer really
changed completely.

00:10:13.650 --> 00:10:15.370 align:middle line:84%
Educated as a
Christian, of course,

00:10:15.370 --> 00:10:20.710 align:middle line:84%
I was praying to the holy mother
Mary or to Jesus and the cross.

00:10:20.710 --> 00:10:23.920 align:middle line:84%
In the meantime, I prayed
to what I call God.

00:10:23.920 --> 00:10:27.340 align:middle line:84%
All true, I have no
definition of God.

00:10:27.340 --> 00:10:33.640 align:middle line:84%
I read quite some intelligent
books about what is God.

00:10:33.640 --> 00:10:36.730 align:middle line:84%
None of these scientists was
able to make a definition

00:10:36.730 --> 00:10:39.440 align:middle line:90%
of God, but our little spirit--

00:10:39.440 --> 00:10:42.070 align:middle line:84%
our little
understanding says there

00:10:42.070 --> 00:10:43.720 align:middle line:90%
is a beginning of the universe.

00:10:43.720 --> 00:10:48.650 align:middle line:84%
There must be creation, and
this is what we call God.

00:10:48.650 --> 00:10:52.411 align:middle line:84%
I call it today, the
spirit of the universe.

00:10:52.411 --> 00:11:03.490 align:middle line:90%


00:11:03.490 --> 00:11:09.550 align:middle line:84%
First, I read as many books
as possible, concerning

00:11:09.550 --> 00:11:11.570 align:middle line:90%
the beginning of the religions.

00:11:11.570 --> 00:11:15.490 align:middle line:84%
So how did the Sumerian
religion begin?

00:11:15.490 --> 00:11:18.940 align:middle line:84%
How did the Egyptian
religion begin?

00:11:18.940 --> 00:11:23.050 align:middle line:90%
How did the Maya religion begin?

00:11:23.050 --> 00:11:28.610 align:middle line:84%
And then being critical, and
saying what's going on here?

00:11:28.610 --> 00:11:32.740 align:middle line:84%
Give you an example every
culture has its calendar,

00:11:32.740 --> 00:11:35.230 align:middle line:84%
and every calendar
has a starting point.

00:11:35.230 --> 00:11:36.040 align:middle line:90%
We're Christian.

00:11:36.040 --> 00:11:38.770 align:middle line:84%
We have a Christian calendar,
and the starting point

00:11:38.770 --> 00:11:41.530 align:middle line:90%
was the birth of Jesus Christ.

00:11:41.530 --> 00:11:45.400 align:middle line:84%
So the starting point is
always very, very important

00:11:45.400 --> 00:11:48.400 align:middle line:84%
for the certain culture
because you just don't

00:11:48.400 --> 00:11:50.980 align:middle line:90%
start the calender for nothing.

00:11:50.980 --> 00:11:53.050 align:middle line:84%
The same thing happened
in Central America.

00:11:53.050 --> 00:11:54.850 align:middle line:84%
There's the calendar
of the Maya,

00:11:54.850 --> 00:12:02.200 align:middle line:84%
and the Mayan calendar starts
on August 11th 3114 BC.

00:12:02.200 --> 00:12:06.040 align:middle line:84%
So asking myself,
what was the reason?

00:12:06.040 --> 00:12:10.120 align:middle line:84%
Why I have they started their
Maya calendar on August 11,

00:12:10.120 --> 00:12:12.250 align:middle line:90%
3114 BC?

00:12:12.250 --> 00:12:14.810 align:middle line:90%
What was so important?

00:12:14.810 --> 00:12:18.200 align:middle line:84%
When the Spanish conqueror
arrived in Central America,

00:12:18.200 --> 00:12:20.350 align:middle line:84%
